===Etymology===
From {{com|en|god|fearing}}, likely an alteration of {{der|en|enm|goddfrihti|t=god-fearing|lit=god-frighty}} and {{m|enm|god-friht|t=god-fearing}} (whence modern {{cog|en|god-fright}}), from {{der|en|ang|godfyrht|t=god-fearing}}. Compare {{noncog|goh|gotforht|t=god-fearing}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Acting with [[obedience]] to rules established by a [[deity]] out of [[fear]] of the [[power]] of that deity.
# {{1|devout}}; [[pious]]; very [[religious]].

